.SH NAME
AudioContext.suspend \- AudioContext: suspend() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]suspend()\f[R] method of the \f[CR]AudioContext\f[R] Interface
suspends the progression of time in the audio context, temporarily
halting audio hardware access and reducing CPU/battery usage in the
process \[em] this is useful if you want an application to power down
the audio hardware when it will not be using an audio context for a
while.
.PP
This method will cause an \f[CR]INVALID_STATE_ERR\f[R] exception to be
thrown if called on an \f[CR]OfflineAudioContext\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
suspend()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that resolves with \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
The promise is rejected if the context has already been closed.
